author: Kim LaCapria
title: Reginald VelJohnson Death Hoax
text:
'Family Matters' star Reginald VelJohnson is alive and tweeting. 0 'Family Matters' star Reginald VelJohnson died of a heart attack in February 2017. See Example(s) EXAMPLES Collected via Twitter, February 2017 
The rumor is that Reginald Valjohnson from the TV show Family Matters has passed away. Damn #ReginaldVelJohnson thanks u made my childhoold watching black family doing it right growing up #CarlWinslow #RIPReginaldVelJohnson 
â Tyson Curtis (@CuRecka) February 15, 2017 #RIP : We’ve just learned that #ReginaldVelJohnson , best known as Carl Winslow on #FamilyMatters , has passed away… https://t.co/YNsEJdiLit 
â Kathy Semble (@PrintasticGames) February 16, 2017 false false ORIGIN 
On 13 February 2017, the web site HeadlinenNews.comÂ reported Â that Reginald VelJohnson (best known for his role as Carl Winslow onÂ “Family Matters”) had died of a heart attack: 
Reginald Vel Johnson, the actor best known as Family Mattersâ Carl Winslow, has died after suffering a heart attack. He was 64. 
He was loved by the world and he will be missed profoundly,â says Jenkins, 24. âOur entire family thanks you for your thoughts and prayers.â 
Rumors claim that Vel Johnson was flying from London to Los Angeles on Sunday, Feb. 12, when he went into cardiac arrest. According to the story, paramedics removed him from the flight and rushed him to a nearby hospital, where he was treated for a heart attack. 
The rumor was given traction by VelJohnson’s appearance in a meme mocking the non-existent “ Bowling Green Massacre “: 
VelJohnson personally debunked the claims on Twitter: Twitter literally trying to kill me! đđđ https://t.co/OdRTRJVi7f 
â Reginald VelJohnson (@rveljohnson) February 15, 2017 Even when I finally pass you can still contact me thru this clock. Photo credit: some weirdo lol pic.twitter.com/ktLhkH83VF 
â Reginald VelJohnson (@rveljohnson) February 15, 2017 
Although VelJohnson’s Twitter account isÂ not verified, it was registered in 2009 and was not likely to be operating as a separate hoax. Even if it were a hoax Twitter account, however, the difficult-to-find “ About ” page on HeadlinenNews.com has the following disclaimer: 
Headlinen News is a satire site. We use real people to make real funny stories. Chill folks, its all for fun.
